1. Git-native first.
2. Bash + git only.
3. Self-documenting CLI.
4. Docs, code, tests, and skill stay in sync.
5. Test with real agents.
6. Branch for features.
7. Agent-native by default.
8. Dogfood the tool while building it.
9. Prefer jj workspaces over git worktrees for parallel local work in this repo. The git-worktree migration created split-brain local state; jj workspaces fit the intended workflow better.
